TITLE: Michigan State University shooter Anthony McRae found dead after caller's tip to police, officials say
SUMMARY: A tip from a member of the public led Lansing law enforcement to the man who opened fire on Michigan State University, killing three students and critically wounding five more.

TITLE: NYC U-Haul rampage suspect with violent past yet to be charged in attack that killed 1, injured 8 others
SUMMARY: New York City charges are pending against U-Haul rampage suspect Weng Sor, who family says had a history of mental health issues, convictions for stabbings before the Brooklyn attack.

TITLE: Michigan State shooting: Doctor breaks down in tears describing response
SUMMARY: E.W. Sparrow Hospital acting president Dr. Denny Martin broke down in tears on Tuesday morning while providing updates on the five victims of the mass shooting at Michigan State University.

TITLE: Portland's Police Bureau is reviewing officer's use of force in car theft case
SUMMARY: An Oregon police officer's use of force while responding to a report of a stolen car is being reviewed by the Portland Police Bureau. The man allegedly tried to drive away from police.

TITLE: Georgia cities compelled to enforce bans on public camping, could lead to designated areas for the homeless
SUMMARY: Bans on public camping or sleeping by homeless people may be enforced in Georgia. This would potentially lead to designated camping areas for homeless people.

TITLE: Woman dies after being run over by forklift at Florida motel, authorities say
SUMMARY: A woman has died after being run over by a forklift at a Florida beachside motel, authorities said. She has only been identified as someone living at the motel who was 62 years old.

TITLE: Body of Utah teen recovered after he fell through ice at reservoir
SUMMARY: A 14-year-old Utah teen who fell through the ice at the Settlement Canyon Reservoir in Tooele has died after rescuers located the boy's body, authorities said.

TITLE: Ohio residents fear train derailment poisoned air, ground, report animals dying
SUMMARY: Officials say it is safe for Ohio residents to return home after a train derailment in East Palestine caused toxic chemical to spill into the environment, but residents report sick and dying animals.

TITLE: Michigan State shooting: Students describe tense scenes: 'Her hands were completely covered in blood'
SUMMARY: Students at Michigan State University are describing the chaotic scenes on campus Monday night as a mass shooting unfolded that left three dead and five injured.

SUMMARY: Storm systems developing this week could lead to blizzard conditions from the Plains to the Great Lakes and spread snow and rain from the Gulf Coast to the Ohio Valley.

TITLE: Family of Wisconsin police officer who was killed in gun battle speaks at his funeral
SUMMARY: Peter Jerving was a Massachusetts police officer who was shot and killed in a gun battle with a robbery suspect. His family praised him at his funeral on Monday.

TITLE: Boston's mayor files plan to address city's skyrocketing rent
SUMMARY: Michelle Wu, the mayor of Boston, is addressing the rent price increase in the city. The mayor filed a proposal that would exempt owner-occupied properties with six or less units.

SUMMARY: The shooting Monday at Michigan State University left five people in a hospital in critical condition, according to officials. Three people died in the shooting.

SUMMARY: Three people were killed when a gunman opened fire inside an academic hall at Michigan State University on Monday evening, according to police.

SUMMARY: Former Clarke County, Alabama, Sheriff William Ray Norris had an 11-count indictment against him reinstated by an appellate court for campaign finance and ethics charges.

TITLE: Michigan sheriff worried woman charged in college student's hit-and-run death will try avoiding extradition
SUMMARY: The Michigan sheriff overseeing an investigation into a fatal hit-and-run says he's "absolutely" concerned the suspect will attempt to avoid extradition.

SUMMARY: A South Carolina man who stabbed his wife 14 times and killed her, was sentenced to life in prison by a Dorchester County judge last week.
